}</script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/03~yq9q893hmn.js\" noModule=\"\"></script></head><body class=\"instrument_sans_f11a402-module__eb3qEq__variable fraunces_c34708e9-module__0Tq2Na__variable antialiased nv-body nv-page\"><div hidden=\"\"><!--$--><!--/$--></div><div id=\"temp-wrapper\"><!--$--><nav class=\"sticky top-0 z-[100] border-b border-slate-200 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur\"><div class=\"mx-auto flex h-14 max-w-7xl items-center justify-between px-4 sm:px-6\"><div class=\"h-8 w-28 rounded-full bg-slate-200\"></div><div class=\"hidden h-9 w-40 rounded-full bg-slate-200 lg:block\"></div></div></nav><!--/$--><div id=\"container-1606e7870f004d67136f85f2b1698cd3\"></div><div class=\"nv-route-chrome\"><div aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"nv-route-ornament\"></div><div class=\"nv-route-content\"><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"CollectionPage\",\"name\":\"Baby Names with Meanings — Islamic, Hindu & Christian Names A–Z\",\"description\":\"Discover 65,000+ baby names with authentic meanings, origins & lucky numbers across Islamic Quranic, Christian Biblical, and Hindu Sanskrit traditions.\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names\",\"about\":{\"@type\":\"Thing\",\"name\":\"Baby Names by Religion\"},\"mainEntity\":{\"@type\":\"ItemList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Islamic Names\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/religion/islamic/1\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Christian Names\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/religion/christian/1\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":3,\"name\":\"Hindu Names\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/religion/hindu/1\"}]}}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Baby Names\",\"item\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names\"}]}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"WebSite\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\",\"potentialAction\":{\"@type\":\"SearchAction\",\"target\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/?q={search_term_string}\",\"query-input\":\"required name=search_term_string\"}}</script><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\",\"logo\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/logo.png\",\"sameAs\":[\"https://twitter.com/nameverse\",\"https://facebook.com/nameverse\"]}</script><div class=\"w-full\"><section class=\"relative bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-50 via-white to-blue-50 dark:from-gray-900 dark:via-gray-800 dark:to-gray-900 pt-6 pb-12 overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"absolute inset-0 opacity-30 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_1px_1px,rgba(16,185,129,0.3)_1px,transparent_0)] bg-[size:24px_24px]\"></div><div class=\"relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4\"><nav class=\"mb-6\" aria-label=\"Breadcrumb\"><ol class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-gray-500\"><li><a class=\"text-emerald-600 hover:text-emerald-800 font-medium transition-colors\" href=\"/\">Home</a></li><li class=\"text-gray-300\">/</li><li class=\"text-gray-700 font-semibold\" aria-current=\"page\">Cultural Name Knowledge Base</li></ol></nav><h1 class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4 leading-tight tracking-tight\">Cultural Name Knowledge Base —<!-- --> <span class=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-600 via-blue-600 to-orange-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent\">Linguistic Origin Analysis Across Civilizations</span></h1><p class=\"text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mb-8 leading-relaxed\">65,000+ personal names with linguistic origin analysis across Islamic (Arabic/Semitic), Christian (Hebrew/Aramaic/Greek), and Hindu (Sanskrit/Dravidian) traditions — plus 21,000+ cross-cultural names. Each entry includes root etymology, phonetic structure, and cultural semantic interpretation.</p><div class=\"flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-2\"><div class=\"flex items-center gap-2 bg-white/80 dark:bg-gray-800/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl px-4 py-2.5 shadow-sm border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700\"><div class=\"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500\"></div><span class=\"text-sm font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white\">18,000+</span><span class=\"text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400\">Islamic Onomastics</span></div><div class=\"flex items-center gap-2 bg-white/80 dark:bg-gray-800/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl px-4 py-2.5 shadow-sm border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700\"><div class=\"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-blue-500\"></div><span class=\"text-sm font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white\">11,000+</span><span class=\"text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400\">Christian Onomastics</span></div><div class=\"flex items-center gap-2 bg-white/80 dark:bg-gray-800/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl px-4 py-2.5 shadow-sm border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700\"><div class=\"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-orange-500\"></div><span class=\"text-sm font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white\">15,000+</span><span class=\"text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400\">Hindu Onomastics</span></div><div class=\"flex items-center gap-2 bg-white/80 dark:bg-gray-800/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl px-4 py-2.5 shadow-sm border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700\"><div class=\"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-purple-500\"></div><span class=\"text-sm font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white\">21,000+</span><span class=\"text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400\">Cross-Cultural</span></div></div></div></section><div class=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 -mt-6 relative z-10 mb-16\"><div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6\"><div class=\"rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-950/30 border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 hover:scale-[1.02] group relative overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"absolute top-0 right-0 w-32 h-32 opacity-5\"><div class=\"w-full h-full rounded-full bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 blur-3xl\"></div></div><div class=\"flex justify-between items-start mb-3\"><span class=\"text-4xl\">🕌</span><span class=\"text-xs font-mono bg-white/50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 font-semibold\">18,000+ names | 98% verified</span></div><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-gray-900 dark:text-white\">📖 Islamic Names — Arabic &amp; Semitic Linguistic Analysis</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3\">Names of Arabic, Persian, and Urdu linguistic origin with etymological analysis, Quranic context, and cultural semantic interpretation across Islamic civilizations.</p><p class=\"text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 text-xs leading-relaxed mb-5 border-l-2 border-purple-300 pl-3 italic\">Explore 18,000+ personal names from Islamic linguistic tradition with scholarly verification of root etymology, phonetic structure, and cross-cultural usage patterns including names popular in 2026.</p><div class=\"flex gap-2 mb-3\"><a class=\"flex-1 text-center text-xs font-semibold py-2.5 px-3 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 hover:border-purple-300 hover:text-purple-700 dark:hover:text-purple-400 transition-all\" href=\"/islamic/boy-names\">♂ Masculine Names</a><a class=\"flex-1 text-center text-xs font-semibold py-2.5 px-3 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 hover:border-purple-300 hover:text-purple-700 dark:hover:text-purple-400 transition-all\" href=\"/islamic/girl-names\">♀ Feminine Names</a></div><a class=\"block w-full text-center bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-900 dark:text-white font-semibold py-3 px-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:border-purple-300 transition-all group-hover:shadow-md text-sm\" href=\"/names/religion/islamic/1\">All Islamic Names →</a></div><div class=\"rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950/30 border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 hover:scale-[1.02] group relative overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"absolute top-0 right-0 w-32 h-32 opacity-5\"><div class=\"w-full h-full rounded-full bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 blur-3xl\"></div></div><div class=\"flex justify-between items-start mb-3\"><span class=\"text-4xl\">⛪</span><span class=\"text-xs font-mono bg-white/50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 font-semibold\">11,000+ names | Biblical sources</span></div><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-gray-900 dark:text-white\">✝️ Christian Names — Hebrew, Aramaic &amp; Greek Etymologies</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3\">Names of Biblical Hebrew, Aramaic, Greek, and Latin linguistic origin with etymological context from Old and New Testament sources and early Christian traditions.</p><p class=\"text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 text-xs leading-relaxed mb-5 border-l-2 border-purple-300 pl-3 italic\">Discover 11,000+ personal names from Christian linguistic tradition — including Biblical names, virtue names, and apostolic names — with root etymology and historical evolution analysis.</p><div class=\"flex gap-2 mb-3\"><a class=\"flex-1 text-center text-xs font-semibold py-2.5 px-3 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 hover:border-purple-300 hover:text-purple-700 dark:hover:text-purple-400 transition-all\" href=\"/christian/boy-names\">♂ Masculine Names</a><a class=\"flex-1 text-center text-xs font-semibold py-2.5 px-3 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 hover:border-purple-300 hover:text-purple-700 dark:hover:text-purple-400 transition-all\" href=\"/christian/girl-names\">♀ Feminine Names</a></div><a class=\"block w-full text-center bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-900 dark:text-white font-semibold py-3 px-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:border-purple-300 transition-all group-hover:shadow-md text-sm\" href=\"/names/religion/christian/1\">All Christian Names →</a></div><div class=\"rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 bg-orange-50 dark:bg-orange-950/30 border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 hover:scale-[1.02] group relative overflow-hidden\"><div class=\"absolute top-0 right-0 w-32 h-32 opacity-5\"><div class=\"w-full h-full rounded-full bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 blur-3xl\"></div></div><div class=\"flex justify-between items-start mb-3\"><span class=\"text-4xl\">🔱</span><span class=\"text-xs font-mono bg-white/50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 font-semibold\">15,000+ names | Vedic sources</span></div><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-gray-900 dark:text-white\">🕉️ Hindu Names — Sanskrit &amp; Dravidian Linguistic Origins</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3\">Names of Sanskrit, Vedic, and Dravidian linguistic origin with etymological analysis, cultural context from Hindu traditions, and phonetic structure documentation.</p><p class=\"text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 text-xs leading-relaxed mb-5 border-l-2 border-purple-300 pl-3 italic\">Browse 15,000+ personal names from Hindu linguistic tradition — including Vedic names, deity-associated names, and nature-derived names — with root etymology and regional variations.</p><div class=\"flex gap-2 mb-3\"><a class=\"flex-1 text-center text-xs font-semibold py-2.5 px-3 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 hover:border-purple-300 hover:text-purple-700 dark:hover:text-purple-400 transition-all\" href=\"/hindu/boy-names\">♂ Masculine Names</a><a class=\"flex-1 text-center text-xs font-semibold py-2.5 px-3 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 hover:border-purple-300 hover:text-purple-700 dark:hover:text-purple-400 transition-all\" href=\"/hindu/girl-names\">♀ Feminine Names</a></div><a class=\"block w-full text-center bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-900 dark:text-white font-semibold py-3 px-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:border-purple-300 transition-all group-hover:shadow-md text-sm\" href=\"/names/religion/hindu/1\">All Hindu Names →</a></div></div></div><section class=\"max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 mb-16\"><div class=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-50 via-white to-blue-50 dark:from-gray-800 dark:via-gray-800 dark:to-gray-800 rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-10 shadow-sm border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700\"><h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6 text-center\">Cross-Cultural Onomastics Research — 65,000+ Personal Names</h2><div class=\"space-y-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed\"><p>NameVerse is a Cultural Name Knowledge Base providing linguistic origin analysis for personal names across civilizations. Whether researching <a class=\"text-emerald-600 hover:underline font-medium\" href=\"/islamic/boy-names\">Islamic masculine names</a> with Arabic/Semitic roots, <a class=\"text-blue-600 hover:underline font-medium\" href=\"/christian/girl-names\">Christian feminine names</a> of Biblical Hebrew origin, or <a class=\"text-orange-600 hover:underline font-medium\" href=\"/hindu/boy-names\">Hindu masculine names</a> with Sanskrit etymology — our database of 65,000+ entries covers every major linguistic tradition.</p><p>Each entry includes linguistic origin, root etymology, cultural semantic interpretation, gender classification, phonetic structure, and cross-cultural usage data. Our scholarly verification process references: Quranic Arabic and classical dictionaries for Islamic names, Biblical Hebrew/Greek concordances for Christian names, and Sanskrit etymological references for Hindu names.</p><p>Start your research by exploring <a class=\"text-emerald-600 hover:underline font-medium\" href=\"/names/religion/islamic/1\">Islamic onomastics</a>,<!-- --> <a class=\"text-blue-600 hover:underline font-medium\" href=\"/names/religion/christian/1\">Christian onomastics</a>, or<!-- --> <a class=\"text-orange-600 hover:underline font-medium\" href=\"/names/religion/hindu/1\">Hindu onomastics</a>.<!-- --> <!-- -->Browse by phonetic index (A–Z) for each linguistic tradition below.</p></div></div></section><section class=\"max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 mb-16\"><h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6 text-center\">Browse by Cultural Tradition &amp; Gender</h2><div class=\"grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-6 gap-3\"><a class=\"bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-950/30 border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800 hover:bg-emerald-100 dark:hover:bg-emerald-900/40 border rounded-xl p-3.5 text-center text-sm font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 transition-all hover:shadow-md hover:scale-[1.03]\" href=\"/islamic/boy-names\">🕌 Islamic Masculine</a><a class=\"bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-950/30 border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800 hover:bg-emerald-100 dark:hover:bg-emerald-900/40 border rounded-xl p-3.5 text-center text-sm font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 transition-all hover:shadow-md hover:scale-[1.03]\" href=\"/islamic/girl-names\">🕌 Islamic Feminine</a><a class=\"bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950/30 border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 hover:bg-blue-100 dark:hover:bg-blue-900/40 border rounded-xl p-3.5 text-center text-sm font-semibold text-gray-800 dark: