ark:border-gray-700 pt-3\",\"children\":\"Hindu personal names primarily originate from Sanskrit (Indo-Aryan branch) and Dravidian language families. Many derive from Vedic literature, Puranic texts, and classical Sanskrit etymological roots with regional variations across the Indian subcontinent.\"}]\n26:[\"$\",\"details\",\"3\",{\"className\":\"group bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700/30 rounded-xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700 overflow-hidden\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"summary\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-5 py-4 text-left text-gray-900 dark:text-white font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-gray-100 dark:hover:bg-gray-700/50 transition-colors list-none\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"pr-4\",\"children\":\"How are name meanings verified for accuracy?\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900/40 flex items-center justify-center text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180\",\"children\":\"▾\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed border-t border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700 pt-3\",\"children\":\"Each name undergoes scholarly verification: Islamic names against Quranic Arabic and classical dictionaries, Christian names against Biblical Hebrew/Greek concordances, and Hindu names against Sanskrit etymological references. Our verification rate exceeds 98% across all traditions.\"}]]}]\n27:[\"$\",\"details\",\"4\",{\"className\":\"group bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700/30 rounded-xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700 overflow-hidden\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"summary\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-5 py-4 text-left text-gray-900 dark:text-white font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-gray-100 dark:hover:bg-gray-700/50 transition-colors list-none\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"pr-4\",\"children\":\"Can I find gender-neutral names across different traditions?\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900/40 flex items-center justify-center text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180\",\"children\":\"▾\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed border-t border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700 pt-3\",\"children\":\"Yes — names like Noor (Arabic/Semitic), Arya (Sanskrit), and Eden (Hebrew) represent cross-cultural personal names found in multiple linguistic traditions. Our database cross-references names appearing in multiple cultural contexts.\"}]]}]\n28:[\"$\",\"details\",\"5\",{\"className\":\"group bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700/30 rounded-xl border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700 overflow-hidden\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"summary\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-5 py-4 text-left text-gray-900 dark:text-white font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-gray-100 dark:hover:bg-gray-700/50 transition-colors list-none\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"pr-4\",\"children\":\"What is the historical evolution of personal names across cultures?\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900/40 flex items-center justify-center text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180\",\"children\":\"▾\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed border-t border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700 pt-3\",\"children\":\"Personal names evolve through linguistic migration, cultural exchange, and historical events. For example, Arabic names spread through Islamic expansion into Persian, Turkish, Urdu, and Malay linguistic communities. Biblical names migrated from Hebrew to Greek to Latin to modern European languages.\"}]]}]\n52:Te37,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the linguistic origin of Islamic names?\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Islamic personal names primarily originate from Arabic and Semitic linguistic traditions, with significant influences from Persian, Turkish, and Urdu. Each name is verified against classical Arabic dictionaries, Quranic references, and historical usage patterns across Islamic civilizations.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"upvoteCount\":0,\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the etymological roots of Christian personal names?\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Christian personal names derive from Biblical Hebrew, Aramaic, Greek, and Latin linguistic traditions. Sources include the Old Testament (Hebrew Bible), New Testament Greek texts, early Christian saints, and medieval European naming traditions.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"upvoteCount\":0,\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What linguistic families do Hindu names come from?\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Hindu personal names primarily originate from Sanskrit (Indo-Aryan branch) and Dravidian language families. Many derive from Vedic literature, Puranic texts, and classical Sanskrit etymological roots with regional variations across the Indian subcontinent.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"upvoteCount\":0,\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How are name meanings verified for accuracy?\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Each name undergoes scholarly verification: Islamic names against Quranic Arabic and classical dictionaries, Christian names against Biblical Hebrew/Greek concordances, and Hindu names against Sanskrit etymological references. Our verification rate exceeds 98% across all traditions.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"upvoteCount\":0,\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Can I find gender-neutral names across different traditions?\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes — names like Noor (Arabic/Semitic), Arya (Sanskrit), and Eden (Hebrew) represent cross-cultural personal names found in multiple linguistic traditions. Our database cross-references names appearing in multiple cultural contexts.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"upvoteCount\":0,\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the historical evolution of personal names across cultures?\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Personal names evolve through linguistic migration, cultural exchange, and historical events. For example, Arabic names spread through Islamic expansion into Persian, Turkish, Urdu, and Malay linguistic communities. Biblical names migrated from Hebrew to Greek to Latin to modern European languages.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-07-14\",\"upvoteCount\":0,\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}}]}29:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$52\"}}]\n2c:null\n2d:[\"$\",\"$L2\",\"H\",{\"href\":\"/names/christian/letter/H/1\",\"className\":\"w-9 h-9 flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg text-sm font-bold transition-all duration-200 bg-white border border-blue-200 text-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-50 hover:shadow-sm hover:scale-110 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-600\",\"aria-label\":\"Christian names starting with H\",\"title\":\"Browse Christian personal names beginning with H\",\"children\":\"H\"}]\n2e:[\"$\",\"$L2\",\"I\",{\"href\":\"/names/christian/letter/I/1\",\"className\":\"w-9 h-9 flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg text-sm font-bold transition-all duration-200 bg-white border border-blue-200 text-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-50 hover:shadow-sm hover:scale-110 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-600\",\"aria-label\":\"Christian names starting with I\",\"title\":\"Browse Christian personal names beginning with I\",\"children\":\"I\"}]\n2f:[\"$\",\"$L2\",\"J\",{\"href\":\"/names/christian/letter/J/1\",\"className\":\"w-9 h-9 flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg text-sm font-bold transition-all duration-200 bg-white border border-blue-200 text-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-50 hover:shadow-sm hover:scale-110 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-600\",\"aria-label\":\"Christian names starting with J\",\"title\":\"Browse Christian personal names beginning with J\",\"children\":\"J\"}]\n30:[\"$\",\"$L2\",\"K\",{\"href\":\"/names/christian/letter/K/1\",\"className\":\"w-9 h-9 flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg text-sm font-bold transition-all duration-200 bg-white border border-blue-200 text-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-50 hover:shadow-sm hover:scale-110 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-600\",\"aria-label\":\"Christian names starting with K\",\"title\":\"Browse Christian personal names beginning with K\",\"children\":\"K\"}]\n31:[\"$\",\"$L2\",\"L\",{\"href\":\"/name